C3 Presents brought the Lollapalooza Festival back to life at Grand Park Chicago in 2005, after making itself prominent in the world of festivals together with the Austin City Limits Music Festival in 2002.
The two events in 2007 each generated $9.8 million and $11.8 million in gross tax days.
These two festivals take place in an urban environment.
"The European model of Melvin Benn is a rural festival, whereas ours is more likely to take place in urban green spaces," says Charlie Jones.
"The aim is to merge these two concepts in one way or another, in order to simultaneously convey the impression of a rural festival in the European and an urban one in the American way."
Vineland is about halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
"The community of Vineland, including the mayor, is gladly taking on the burden of this event," says Charlie Jones.
The latter refuses to disclose the terms of the agreement, but he confirms "that they are sufficiently interesting to invest in such an event and include a festival that hopefully will have a long life."
