Congress agrees to the MIFID directive, which came into force on November 1.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which today ended its session with the Congressional decision in the Senate on the amendments/additional amendments associated with the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressmen and senators, who had pursued in their negotiations and votes the goal of establishing the best possible arrangement that ensures the security of investors and regulates individual entrepreneurial activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market operation.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, the MIFID aims to improve investor protection, increase the level of control by the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promote cooperation between the various supervisory authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive enables both specialised firms and natural or legal persons to offer financial advice and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services firms (ESIS), the consulting firms that partner with investment and brokerage firms of securities.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, so that the regulated circulation markets are added to the multilateral systems of securities trading and the systems for the internationalization of trading orders, which would eventually compete with the current economic players.
The law obliges investment firms to communicate the priorities of their company profile, the confrontation and the ways in which risks are handled in the market, and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Congressional Economic Commission made further changes retrospectively, with the decision that the debt securities must now be considered complex financial resources for the investor due to their high degree of risk has been confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the areas of work of graduate economists was used; 30 years after the 1977 regulation restricting the areas of work reserved for economists was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on behalf of others, does not require authorisation from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and the acquisition of customers to several investment companies at the same time.
The harmonised consumer price index (CPI) rose by five tenths in November and now stands at 4.1%.
The indicator used by Eurostat to assess the inflation rate within the European Union provides the average price trend in Spain in November.
Its publication is in line with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which aim at comparing the location and quality of US products by disclosing the data.
The forecast for the indicator can be made prematurely by applying the same approach as for the harmonised consumer price index, but at the same time using various other statistical modelling methods to estimate the information not available at the time of the calculation.
However, the Spanish Statistical Office (INE) warned that the prematurely determined indicator would only serve as a benchmark and therefore would not have to be in line with the final result, which will be announced on 14 December.
The consumer price index (CPI) will remain at a relatively high level
According to Deputy Head of Government and Minister of Economic Affairs and Finance Pedro Solbes, the increase in the CPI in November is a temporary development, while at the same time ensuring that the price index will remain at a relatively high level in the coming months.
Nevertheless, Solbes noted in the halls of the Congress building that even if the current number is not good, Spain’s inflation difference compared to the other members of the monetary union has remained more or less the same in recent years.
He also explained that there were fewer surprises in November than in the previous month, when the government did not expect such a large increase.
We expected a value of around 4%, the Minister of Economics and Finance announced in view of the forecast published today.
