Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which, in turn, depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of issuance of the driver’s license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the Company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding indemnity in the event of a loss.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance, which is composed of several factors, including age, gender, time of issuance of the driver’s license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contribution payments are due in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make less contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, as they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the company's conviction.
The benefit assigned to the vehicle impairs the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more often the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We now list the most important points to consider when choosing insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing an inexpensive insurance, such as low driving practice and the young driving licence.
Even if it is best to take out full insurance for an ideal insurance coverage, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full insurance with excess, so that the benefits of full insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract involves the customer having to pay part of the amount incurred as a result of the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, main representative of Spain at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to cut insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the base rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depend on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may allow itself to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract because the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Therefore, it is best to opt for full insurance with deductible.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving , explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the fear of the beginner has been discarded.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out full insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person in question also allows.
On the part of insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full insurance with deductible (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which starts only for the third year of the vehicle.
They generally drive more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full-casco insurance with deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs, which require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
